  'help.center': 'Help\nCenter',
  'service.user.rules': '<p>We only encourage payment to be made before you arrange for a meet-and-greet for the security of all parties.</p><p>To ensure fair quotes and to avoid a price war for all Pet Hosts, as well as to further grow the PetBacker community, any pet host who is flagged by our system for any of the following scenarios will only receive selected Public Jobs or be restricted to only Private Jobs. Repeat offender accounts can only be used to make requests.</p><p>These include:<ol><li>Requesting for Cash payment outside the platform</li><li>Requesting customers to make partial payments outside the platform</li><li>Requesting customers to revise a booking from multiple days/visits/walks to one</li><li>Promoting other competitor platforms</li><li>Requesting customers contact you outside by visiting social media before payment</li><li>Exchange of contacts or meet up before booking payment on PetBacker (Penalty of 40% of the Fees to restore your account if you are unable to win the job)</li><li>Giving customers an unreasonable low rate or discount under a pretence that it is a deposit (e.g. USD$1 for a Booking to get contact or to deal outside)</li><li>Cancelling or getting cancelled for a hired booking without good reason</li><li>Subsequent bookings or extensions not made via the platform</li><li>Misleading customers that PetBacker charges fees without informing them about the importance of Pet Insurance that PetBacker includes in the hope they will deal with you outside</li></ol></p><p>Let us know if you need any help or still face any issue.</p><p>P/S: If the customers have not booked you yet, get them to book you and your account restriction will be removed. This will benefit you more than paying the penalty.</p>',
  'faq.listings': '<p>Dear new Backers, Welcome to PetBacker. Below is a guide and a list of Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) for you to better understand how you provide your service with PetBacker.</p><p><strong>FAQs</strong></p><p><strong>Q: How do I get jobs?</strong></p><div style="text-align:center;"><iframe width="100%" max-width="560" max-height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/sT65TELi81g" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p>A: When someone makes a request for your services in your area, you will receive a notification in your email and the app. You can then reply to the person directly from there for free if you are the first 5 persons to reply.</p><p>So do check your emails (or junk emails, and add us to your safe senders list) and the app.</p><p><strong>Q: What do I need to do to have more successful hires?</strong></p><p>A: Just follow these tips and you are on your way.</p><ol><li>Describe yourself and your services as detail as you can</li><li>Add as many photos of you, your pet and your home compound</li><li>Ask your your friends and previous customers to give you reviews on how much you love pets</li><li>Share your listing on social media to spread the word that you are on PetBacker. You can do this later</li></ol><p><strong>Q: Can I share my contact info before being booked?</strong></p><p>A: We have a full featured messaging system in our app for you to talk with pet parents. The AI system will prevent you from responding to other jobs if you share your contact before being reserved with a prepayment.</p><p>Our Process of getting hired is</p><ol><li>Respond to job request with a quote</li><li>Talk to pet owner via the App for final quote</li><li>Request parents to deposit the refundable full payment in their Petbacker balance to reserve you</li><li>Share contact for Meet &amp; greet</li><li>Receive the Pet and Complete the job for payment</li></ol><p><strong>Q: Why I can\'t answer job anymore?</strong></p><p>A: Because of few reasons</p><ol><li>A complaint may have been lodged against you by a pet owner. We want to hear your side of the story.</li><li>You might have been flagged by our AI for communicating or getting booked outside the platform without paying PetBacker Service Fees. Please note that your service fees will increase by <span style="color:red;">10%</span> each time you do that. You will need to provide SOLID PROOF should you feel it was a misunderstanding.</li><li>You don\'t have any references or testimonials from friends, which will make it difficult to win jobs. We want to help you.</li></ol><p><strong>Q: Why make payment on PetBacker?</strong></p><p>A: It is for your protection as well as to ensure pet owners are serious in hiring you. The prepayment is fully refundable to the pet owner if you do not accept the job. Statistics show that when pet owners do not pay ahead they:</p><ol><li>Might not turn up for the meeting, wasting the sitters time</li><li>Might not pay the pet sitter after the job is done</li><li>Might be someone who will abandon the pet as he/she is not interested with the basic pet insurance that comes with payments via PetBacker</li><li>Might be someone who is a scammer and getting your contact for undesirable reasons</li></ol><p>Our platform also needs the funds to operate, advertise and improve. Please remember that it is PETBACKER that has brought you the jobs and these jobs are available to you because of our advertisements and marketing efforts. We need your support by paying us the fees due to us so we can attract more pet owners and help you.</p><p><strong>Q: How does the customer pay me?</strong></p><p>A: Your customers can make payment with credit cards, debit cards or direct bank transfer (in certain countries) through the app before the job starts. After the job is completed, the payment is released to you after a 2 day dispute period or immediately if the pet parent leaves you a good review. Payments will be reflected in your bank account after 2 to 7 banking days.</p><p>Booking and getting paid through PetBacker is required per our Terms of Service and pet service providers who encourage payment outside of PetBacker will be subjected to account restrictions like requiring credits to reply to jobs. Find out more <a href="https://www.petbacker.com/help-center/pet-service-providers/how-do-i-get-paid">here</a>.</p><p><strong>Q: What is a verified review and completed jobs</strong></p><p>A: Verified reviews are special reviews that can <b>be obtained</b> when a job is paid and completed on PetBacker. These reviews carry a lot more credibility when a pet parent is making a decision to hire. You can tell it\'s a verified review as there is a "Verified review" badge on the title of that review.</p><p>For every job paid and completed with PetBacker you gain one \'Completed Job\' point. Statistics show that pet service providers with more \'Completed Job\' points get hired more often.</p><div style="text-align:center;"><img style="max-width: 90%;" src="https://storage.googleapis.com/petbacker/images/cms/verified-review.jpg" /></div><p><strong>Q: How do I become a super backer?</strong></p><p>A: Becoming a super backer is straightforward. The more reviews and jobs you complete, the more extra bonuses you will get for each level which will be announced from time to time.</p><p><strong>Q:  I am below 18, can I do it?</strong></p><p>A: We have a standard minimum age limit of 18 years and above to be a pet service provider with PetBacker. However this may vary based on the local laws of the location where you are from.</p><div style="text-align:center;"><p><a href="https://www.petbacker.com/help-center">Help Center</a></p></div>',
